      "content": "Dizziness is a sign your body is still trying to rebalance, so don't rush into medication yet. Ibuprofen is fine for a lingering ache, but for dizziness, you need to focus on stabilizing your system first. Try sipping on some ginger tea while taking a couple of those ibuprofen tablets, and then lie down in a dark, quiet room for twenty minutes. This combination will gently soothe the nerves and help you focus for your exam.",
